'''英國去留歐盟公投民意調查'''涵蓋英國政府宣布舉行[[英國去留歐盟公投|英國去留歐盟公投]]後至2016年6月23日的公投日期間的所有民意調查，也有部分民調在2010年已開始進行。民調顯示，脫離歐洲聯盟（即脫歐）和留在歐洲聯盟（即留歐）的支持率不相伯仲。至於其他[[欧洲联盟成员国|歐盟成員國]]的非英國國民中，過半數支持英國原則上留歐。但亦有相近比例的受訪者認為，若然英方{{tsl|en|United Kingdom renegotiation of European Union membership, 2015–16|2015－16年英國重新談判歐洲聯盟會籍|重新談判}}後才留歐的話，英國就應脫歐。

== 分析 ==
=== 人口分佈 ===
外界研究民意調查結果後得出以下的結論：

* 較年輕選民傾向支持留歐，但他們不太會去投票<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/apr/02/eu-referendum-young-voters-brexit-leave|title=EU referendum: poll shows young voters could hold key in June vote|author=Toby Helm|date=2016-04-02|accessdate=2016-05-15|work=The Guardian|archive-date=2016-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160510102056/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/apr/02/eu-referendum-young-voters-brexit-leave|dead-url=no}}</ref>；較年長選民則傾向支持脫歐<ref name=":1" />；
* 男女的取態沒有明顯分別<ref name=":1" />；
* 管理層、專業人士和行政人員比較支持留歐；半熟練工人、非技術工人和依賴援助的人士是脫歐派中最大支持群體；
* 大學畢業生比起沒有資歷選民更支持留歐<ref name=":1">{{cite web |url=http://whatukthinks.org/eu/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Analysis-paper-1-Britain-divided.pdf |title=Britain divided? Who supports and who opposes EU membership |author=John Curtice, senior research fellow at NatCen and professor of politics at Strathclyde University |publisher={{tsl|en|Economic and Social Research Council||Economic and Social Research Council}} |date=October 2015 |accessdate=2020-08-26 |archive-date=2020-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200728200250/https://whatukthinks.org/eu/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Analysis-paper-1-Britain-divided.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>；
* 白人選民中脫歐和留歐支持度相若，所有[[少数群体|少數族裔]]傾向支持留歐，但[[登记选民|登記率]]和[[投票率|投票率]]相對較低<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/eu-referendum-outcome-on-a-knife-edge-according-to-new-data-from-british-election-survey-a7034751.html|title=EU referendum outcome on a knife edge, according to latest survey|date=2016-05-18|work=Independent|author=Charlie Cooper|accessdate=2016-05-18|archive-date=2019-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331174615/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/eu-referendum-outcome-on-a-knife-edge-according-to-new-data-from-british-election-survey-a7034751.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>；
* 蘇格蘭國內留歐支持度明顯高於整個英國<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-35602861|title=Is Scotland the most pro-EU part of the UK?|date=2016-02-18|accessdate=2016-05-20|publisher=BBC News|author=Nick Eardley|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202230016/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-35602861|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 取樣方法 ===
外界已知取樣方法會影響民調結果，其中電話訪問的結果通常都是留歐派佔優<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-35926183|title=How to read the EU referendum opinion polls|last=Cook|first=Chris|publisher=BBC News|access-date=2016-05-14|date=2016-03-30|archive-date=2020-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204120622/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-35926183|dead-url=no}}</ref>。使用網上問卷取樣的[[YouGov|YouGov]]就批評電話訪問大學畢業生的比例過高，繼而令結果有誤差<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yougov.co.uk/news/2016/05/20/revealed-evidence-greater-skews-phone-polls/|title=Revealed: new evidence reveals greater skews in phone polls|date=2016-05-20|accessdate=2016-05-21|author=Andy Morris|publisher=YouGov|archive-date=2018-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180215075111/https://yougov.co.uk/news/2016/05/20/revealed-evidence-greater-skews-phone-polls/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。{{tsl|en|Ipsos MORI}}、{{tsl|en|ComRes}}和YouGov前主席{{tsl|en|Peter Kellner|彼得·奇拿}}則認為電話訪問更可信<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/0fa011c4-edb5-11e4-a894-00144feab7de.html|title=Pollsters disagree on who is ahead in UK general election race|date=2015-04-28|author1=Jim Pickard|author2=Kiran Stacey|author3=Gavin Jackson|accessdate=2016-05-17|work=Financial Times|archive-date=2015-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150708212806/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/0fa011c4-edb5-11e4-a894-00144feab7de.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://politicscounter.com/?p=56|title=EU referendum: "remain" on course for clear victory|date=2016-05-20|accessdate=2016-05-21|author=Peter Kellner|website=The Politics Counter|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525134344/http://politicscounter.com/?p=56|archive-date=2016-05-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=EU referendum: All still to play for but not neck and neck|url=http://www.comres.co.uk/eu-referendum-all-still-to-play-for-by-not-neck-and-neck/|date=2015-12-16|accessdate=2016-05-21|publisher=ComRes|archive-date=2016-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701122225/http://www.comres.co.uk/eu-referendum-all-still-to-play-for-by-not-neck-and-neck/|dead-url=no}}</ref>；2016年3月{{Tsl|en|Populus Ltd|Populus (公司)|Populus}}和{{tsl|en|Number Cruncher Politics||Number Cruncher Politics}}的聯合研究發現電話訪問更能夠反映某議題的公眾意見<ref>{{cite web|title=Polls apart|url=http://www.populus.co.uk/2016/03/polls-apart/|accessdate=2016-05-17|date=2016-03-29|publisher=Populus|author1=Matt Singh|author2=James Kanagasooriam|archive-date=2018-12-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181214124014/http://www.populus.co.uk/2016/03/polls-apart/|dead-url=no}}</ref>；{{tsl|en|ICM Research|ICM研究中心}}則指出正確答案介乎電話民調和網上民調之間<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/16/phone-poll-finds-10-point-lead-for-remain-but-web-survey-puts-leave-ahead-brexit|date=2016-05-16|title=Phone survey finds 10-point lead for remain but web poll puts leave ahead|author=Tom Clark|accessdate=2016-05-17|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108165900/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/16/phone-poll-finds-10-point-lead-for-remain-but-web-survey-puts-leave-ahead-brexit|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

不過是次公投和[[2015年英國大選|2015年大選]]都揭露民調取樣方法仍然有瑕疵，但總體而言網上問卷的準確度較高。平均而言，網上民調估計脫歐派以1.2%之差勝出，而電話訪問則估計留歐派會以2.6%之差勝出<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/brexit-polls-missed_us_576cb63fe4b017b379f58610|title=How Brexit Polls Missed The 'Leave' Victory|date=2016-06-24|newspaper=[[赫芬顿邮报|The Huffington Post]]|author=Natalie Jackson|accessdate=2020-08-26|archive-date=2017-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119102317/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/brexit-polls-missed_us_576cb63fe4b017b379f58610|dead-url=no}}</ref>。觀乎所有民調的話，63%的網上問卷預測脫歐為戰果，相反78%的電話訪問認為是相反<ref name="fred">{{cite website|url=https://yougov.co.uk/news/2016/06/28/online-polls-were-right/|title=The online polls were RIGHT, and other lessons from the referendum|date=2016-06-28|website=Yougov|author=Freddie Sayers|accessdate=2020-08-26|archive-date=2017-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171122094708/https://yougov.co.uk/news/2016/06/28/online-polls-were-right/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。選前唯二評估脫歐派勝出的{{tsl|en|Kantar TNS}}和Opinium都是使用網上問卷形式<ref name="fred" />。

=== 民調之民調 ===
數個組織收集不同機構的民調後取其平均作為「民調之民調」，計算方法各有不同，例如較近期的民調比重較重，又或者調整電話和網上民調的結果以收窄兩種採樣的結果差異，因此不同的「民調之民調」會有不同的結果。

