== 專業團體民調 ==

=== 商界領袖 ===
{{tsl|en|British Chambers of Commerce|英國總商會}}在2016年1月和2月訪問了2,200名商界領袖，當中六成人支持留歐、三成人支持脫歐。到5月的民調，比例收窄為54%比37%<ref>{{cite news|last1=Elliott|first1=Larry|title=Business support for EU membership has fallen in run-up to vote|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/may/10/eu-referendum-business-leaders-remain-brexit-bcc-survey|accessdate=2016-05-14|work=The Guardian|date=2016-05-09|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108114001/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/may/10/eu-referendum-business-leaders-remain-brexit-bcc-survey|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=BCC EU Survey: Business vote tightens as referendum campaign heads to the finish line|url=http://www.britishchambers.org.uk/press-office/press-releases/bcc-eu-survey-business-vote-tightens-as-referendum-campaign-heads-to-the-finish-line.html|publisher=britishchambers.org.uk|accessdate=2016-05-14|archive-date=2017-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708162712/http://www.britishchambers.org.uk/press-office/press-releases/bcc-eu-survey-business-vote-tightens-as-referendum-campaign-heads-to-the-finish-line.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。{{tsl|en|Confederation of British Industry|英國工業總會}}委託{{tsl|en|ComRes}}所作的民調表示，八成認為留歐對營商未來最好，相反只有5%認為脫歐最好<ref>{{cite news|last1=Inman|first1=Phillip|title=CBI member survey reveals huge support for remaining in EU|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/mar/15/cbi-member-survey-reveals-huge-support-for-remaining-in-eu|accessdate=2016-05-14|work=The Guardian|date=2016-03-15|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108192453/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/mar/15/cbi-member-survey-reveals-huge-support-for-remaining-in-eu|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Chu|first1=Ben|title=EU referendum: CBI warns Brexit could blow £100bn hole in economy and cost 950,000 jobs|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-could-blow-a-100bn-hole-in-the-uk-economy-and-cost-up-to-950000-jobs-cbi-warns-a6942846.html|website=The Independent|accessdate=2016-05-14|language=en-GB|date=2016-03-21|archive-date=2019-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331170354/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-could-blow-a-100bn-hole-in-the-uk-economy-and-cost-up-to-950000-jobs-cbi-warns-a6942846.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=CBI to make economic case to remain in EU after reaffirming strong member mandate – CBI|url=http://news.cbi.org.uk/news/cbi-to-make-economic-case-to-remain-in-eu-after-reaffirming-strong-member-mandate/|website=news.cbi.org.uk|publisher=Confederation of British Industry|accessdate=2016-05-14|archive-date=2016-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160804185405/http://news.cbi.org.uk/news/cbi-to-make-economic-case-to-remain-in-eu-after-reaffirming-strong-member-mandate/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年6月一個民調訪問了英國商界350名董事，當中82%受訪者認同「英國的歐盟會籍對英國商界是好事」，12%不認同<ref>{{cite web|title=Growth Climate Index, Report #1|url=http://www.businessgrowthfund.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/BGF_GCI_Report_FINAL.pdf|website=businessgrowthfund.co.uk/|publisher=Business Growth Fund|accessdate=2016-05-14|archive-date=2017-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702204800/http://www.businessgrowthfund.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/BGF_GCI_Report_FINAL.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="telegraph_business">{{cite news|last1=Burn-Callander|first1=Rebecca|title=British business leaders lose resolve to stay in the EU|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2016/03/29/british-business-leaders-lose-resolve-to-stay-in-the-eu/|accessdate=2016-05-14|work=The Telegraph|date=2016-03-29|archive-date=2019-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331201722/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2016/03/29/british-business-leaders-lose-resolve-to-stay-in-the-eu/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。翌年3月的跟進民調則顯示63%認同「英國商界留在歐盟的境況比起脫離歐盟更好」，20%不認同<ref name="telegraph_business" /><ref name="growthclimate3">{{cite web|title=Growth Climate Index #3|url=http://www.businessgrowthfund.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/BGF_GCI_Infographic_Mar2016_FINAL.pdf|publisher=businessgrowthfund.co.uk|accessdate=2016-05-14|date=March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702132927/http://www.businessgrowthfund.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/BGF_GCI_Infographic_Mar2016_FINAL.pdf|archive-date=2017-07-02|dead-url=yes}}</ref>；而59%認同「脫離歐盟抑制英國商界發展」，30%不認同；71%認同「歐盟會籍讓英國商界進入寶貴的歐洲市場」，16%不認同；35%同意「脫歐令英國商界面臨技術短缺」，50%不同意<ref name="growthclimate3" />。

{{tsl|en|Make UK|工程界僱員聯會}}在2015年下旬委託[[捷孚凯|捷孚凯]]訪問500名廠商高層決策者，當中63%希望英國留歐、5%希望脫歐；3%表示留歐沒有好處，50%則認為留歐重要，另外20%表示留歐對營商極其重要<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eef.org.uk/about-eef/media-news-and-insights/media-releases/2016/feb/six-in-ten-eef-members-want-the-uk-to-remain-in-the-eu|title=Six in ten EEF members want the UK to remain in the EU|date=2016-02-22|website=EEF|access-date=2016-05-23|archive-date=2016-06-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625183002/https://www.eef.org.uk/about-eef/media-news-and-insights/media-releases/2016/feb/six-in-ten-eef-members-want-the-uk-to-remain-in-the-eu|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/feb/22/most-business-leaders-will-vote-to-stay-in-eu-polls-find|title=Most business leaders will vote to stay in EU, polls find|last=Macalister|first=Terry|date=2016-02-22|website=The Guardian|access-date=2016-05-23|archive-date=2020-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130004954/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/feb/22/most-business-leaders-will-vote-to-stay-in-eu-polls-find|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[德勤|德勤]]的兩個民調一共訪問了120名英國大公司的首席財務總監「英國留歐是否符合英國商界利益」，2015年第四季的民調顯示有62%同意、6%不同意，另外有28%表示會待英歐重新談判後再表態；而2016年初的第二場民調則顯示有75%同意、8%不同意<ref>{{cite news|last1=Allen|first1=Katie|title=UK finance chiefs delay hiring and investment as Brexit tops risk list|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/apr/04/uk-finance-chiefs-brexit-tops-risk-list|accessdate=2016-05-14|work=The Guardian|date=2016-04-03|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108141012/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/apr/04/uk-finance-chiefs-brexit-tops-risk-list|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Deloitte CFO Survey: 2016 Q1|url=http://www2.deloitte.com/uk/en/pages/finance/articles/deloitte-cfo-survey.html|publisher=Deloitte.com|accessdate=2016-05-14|archive-date=2021-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115141504/https://www2.deloitte.com/uk/en/pages/finance/articles/deloitte-cfo-survey.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[國際商會|國際商會]]訪問了來自27個不同國家的226間公司，並在2016年4月公佈結果。當中46%表示英國脫歐後將減少當地的投資，1%表示會增加投資；另外86%受訪公司希望英國留歐，8%支持英國脫歐<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kleinman|first1=Mark|title=Brexit Threat To UK Jobs, ICC Survey Warns|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1676669/brexit-threat-to-uk-jobs-icc-survey-warns|accessdate=2016-05-14|publisher=Sky News|date=2016-04-11|language=en-GB|archive-date=2016-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617034413/http://news.sky.com/story/1676669/brexit-threat-to-uk-jobs-icc-survey-warns|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Cordell|first1=Jake|title=EU business leaders: Don't go for Brexit|url=http://www.cityam.com/238675/eu-referendum-business-leaders-tell-david-cameron-that-europe-needs-britain-in-one-more-warning-on-brexit|accessdate=2016-05-14|work=City AM|date=2016-04-12|archive-date=2019-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331170325/http://www.cityam.com/238675/eu-referendum-business-leaders-tell-david-cameron-that-europe-needs-britain-in-one-more-warning-on-brexit|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=86% of international businesses surveyed believe the UK should remain within the EU – says ICC United Kingdom|url=https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0898/9972/files/Press_Release_2016-04-12_ICC_UK_Survey_Results.pdf?6519071907519500121|website=iccwbo.uk|publisher=United Kingdom office of International Chamber of Commerce|accessdate=2016-05-14|date=2016-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223233754/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0898/9972/files/Press_Release_2016-04-12_ICC_UK_Survey_Results.pdf?6519071907519500121|archive-date=2016-12-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

[[金杜律师事务所|金杜律师事务所]]在同年5月公佈訪問了300間公司的調查結果（法德意西各75間），當中68%表示英國脫歐會為他們生意帶來負面影響，62%表示較不可能在英國營商。被問及英國脫歐對自己生意如何得益時，法國、意大利和西班牙的大部分受訪公司認為英國職位將流失至他們本國<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cordell|first1=Jake|title=EU businesses want a hard line in any post-Brexit negotiations|url=http://www.cityam.com/240845/eu-referendum-eu-businesses-say-brexit-will-hurt-them-but-they-want-a-tough-stance-in-any-post-brexit-trade-negotiations|accessdate=2016-05-14|work=City AM|date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2019-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330084433/http://www.cityam.com/240845/eu-referendum-eu-businesses-say-brexit-will-hurt-them-but-they-want-a-tough-stance-in-any-post-brexit-trade-negotiations|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Brexit: The View From Europe|url=http://www.kwm.com/~/media/SjBerwin/Files/Knowledge/Downloads/uk/2016/05/06/kwm-brexit-the-view-from-europe.ashx|publisher=King & Wood Mallesons|accessdate=2016-05-14|archive-date=2017-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170717232929/http://www.kwm.com/~/media/SjBerwin/Files/Knowledge/Downloads/uk/2016/05/06/kwm-brexit-the-view-from-europe.ashx|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 科學界 ===
《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》期刊訪問907名活躍的科研學者，當中78%表示脫歐認為脫歐對英國科學界「某程度上有害」或「非常有害」，9%認為「某程度上有利」或「非常有利」。被問及英國應該脫歐還是留歐時，12%選擇前者、83%選擇後者<ref name="nature30mar16">{{cite journal|last1=Cressey|first1=Daniel|title=Scientists say 'no' to UK exit from Europe in Nature poll|journal=Nature|date=2016-03-30|volume=531|issue=7596|pages=559|doi=10.1038/531559a|pmid=27029257|bibcode=2016Natur.531..559C}}</ref>。期刊亦訪問了另外954名駐紮英國以外歐盟成員國的科學家，當中47%認為英國脫歐對歐盟科學界「某程度上有害」或「非常有害」，11.5%為「某程度上有利」或「非常有利」<ref name="nature30mar16" />。

=== 法律界 ===
《{{tsl|en|Legal Week|法律周刊}}》訪問了律師行350名{{tsl|en|Partner (business rank)|合夥人 (公司)|合夥人}}，當中77%表示英國脫歐對[[倫敦市|倫敦城]]的國際金融市場地位帶來「負面」或「非常負面」影響，相反6.2%認為有「正面」影響。59%的合夥人表示脫歐對自己律師行帶來「頗負面」或「非常負面」影響，13%表示「頗正面」或「非常正面」影響<ref>{{cite news|last1=Booth|first1=James|title=Partners overwhelmingly anti-Brexit as confidence in Britain staying in falters|url=http://www.legalweek.com/legal-week/analysis/2448934/partners-overwhelmingly-anti-brexit-as-confidence-in-britain-staying-in-falters|accessdate=2016-05-14|work=Legal Week|date=2016-03-02|archive-date=2016-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610092250/http://www.legalweek.com/legal-week/analysis/2448934/partners-overwhelmingly-anti-brexit-as-confidence-in-britain-staying-in-falters|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 經濟學界 ===
《[[金融时报_(英国)|金融時報]]》訪問105名經濟學者對英國脫歐的看法，並在2016年1月公佈結果。中期而言，72%受訪者認為英國前景負面，7.6%認為前景會更好，17%認為沒有分別<ref>{{cite news|last1=Giles|first1=Chris|last2=Cadman|first2=Emily|title=Economists' forecasts: Brexit would damage growth|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/1a86ab36-afbe-11e5-b955-1a1d298b6250.html|accessdate=2016-05-14|work=Financial Times|date=2016-01-03|archive-date=2016-09-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160913153952/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/1a86ab36-afbe-11e5-b955-1a1d298b6250.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

Ipsos MORI受《[[觀察家報|觀察家報]]》委託訪問[[英國皇家經濟學會|皇家經濟學會]]和{{tsl|en|Society of Business Economists|商業經濟學會}}的639名成員，88%受訪者認為脫歐將對英國未來五年的經濟帶來負面影響，7%認為沒有影響，3%認為有正面影響；另外82%認為脫歐對住戶入息帶來負面影響，9%認為沒有影響，7%認為有正面影響；未來五至十年，72%認為會為英國經濟帶來負面影響，11%認為沒有影響，11%認為有正面影響；73%認為對住戶入息帶來負面影響，13%認為沒有影響，10%認為有正面影響<ref name="IPSOSeconomists">{{cite web|url=https://www.ipsos-mori.com/researchpublications/researcharchive/3739/Economists-Views-on-Brexit.aspx|title=Economists' Views on Brexit|date=2016-05-28|accessdate=2016-05-29|publisher=Ipsos MORI|archive-date=2016-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161110184441/https://www.ipsos-mori.com/researchpublications/researcharchive/3739/Economists-Views-on-Brexit.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Obseconomists">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/28/economists-reject-brexit-boost-cameron|title=Economists overwhelmingly reject Brexit in boost for Cameron|author=Sonia Sodha, Toby Helm and Phillip Inman|date=2016-05-28|accessdate=2016-05-29|newspaper=Observer|archive-date=2019-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513053955/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/28/economists-reject-brexit-boost-cameron|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

